==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thirteen
<hw>Thir"teen`</hw> <pr>(th⟦etil⟧r"t⟦emac⟧n`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>threttene</ets>, AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧re⟦oacute⟧t⟦emac⟧ne</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧re⟦oacute⟧tyne</ets>.
See <er>Three</er>, and <er>Ten</er>, and cf. <er>Thirty</er>.]</ety>
<def>One more than twelve; ten and three; <as>as, <ex>thirteen</ex>
ounces or pounds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirteen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thirteen
<hw>Thir"teen`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The number greater
by one than twelve; the sum of ten and three; thirteen units or
objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol representing thirteen units, as 13 or
xiii.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thirteenth</ent>⟦br⟧
